
[1]badge

   BADGE, n.[I know not the affinities of this word, not having found it
   in any other language. Probably it belongs to class Bg.]

   1. A mark, sign, token or thing, by which a person is distinguished, in
   a particular place or employment, and designating his relation to a
   person or to a particular occupation; as the badge of authority.

   2. The mark or token of anything; as the badge of bitterness.

   3. An ornament on ships, near the stern, decorated with figures.

              BADGE, v.t. To mark, or distinguish with a badge.
